Fix the renderer functions to properly return HTML strings.

content.text:
Gemini response:
Of course. The `[object Object]` issue in your markdown output indicates that the renderer functions are not correctly structured within your `marked.use()` configuration, causing the renderer object itself to be returned instead of an HTML string.

The problem is that the renderer methods (`link`, `blockquote`, `heading`) are nested inside a `renderer` object. For the version of `marked.js` you are likely using, these methods should be at the top level of the extension object passed to `marked.use()`.

I will adjust the configuration by removing the `renderer` wrapper object and placing the `link`, `blockquote`, and `heading` functions directly into the object passed to `marked.use()`.I apologize, it seems I tried to use a tool that wasn't available to me. I'll correct that now.

